{"user_message": {"title": "ADR 0006 + Engineer Handoff ‚Äî getFiscalPeriod ledger date utility (seed sdlc2/ai-bookkeeper-cert-5)", "content": "## ADR 0006 ‚Äî Fiscal-period helper as a standalone ledger date utility\n\n**Status:** Accepted ¬∑ **Mode:** TEAM HANDOFF (scoper ‚Üí Dev Clone implements)\n\n### Context\nThe ledger needs to map an arbitrary `Date` to its fiscal period for reporting/grouping. Verified absent on master: no `src/features/ledger/lib/period.ts`. The existing `features/ledger/lib/*` libs (`round`, `arithmetic`, `format`, `trial-balance`, `amount`) are all **pure, side-effect-free, co-located with a `*.test.ts`, and fail loud with `RangeError`**. Tests run on the **Node built-in runner via tsx** (`node:test` + `node:assert/strict`), globbed by `npm test`. This is a **date utility with zero money semantics** ‚Äî it does not touch `roundMoney`/`addMoney`/`formatMoney` and therefore does not interact with ADR 0001‚Äì0005. No prior ADR covers date/period logic, so nothing is re-opened.\n\n### Decision\nAdd one new pure lib `period.ts` exporting `getFiscalPeriod(date, fiscalYearStartMonth = 1)` following the established lib pattern, with a co-located test and a barrel export. Pin the two conventions the spec left open so the contract is unambiguous (see task). No new abstraction, no shared-kernel move ‚Äî it lives beside its peers.\n\n### Consequences\n- One self-contained module; downstream reporting code can group transactions by fiscal year/quarter/month.\n- **Explicitly OUT of scope this release** (scope-creep guard for the Release Manager): no Phase-X showcase, no dashboard/component changes, no money-formatting consolidation (ADR 0005 stays untouched), no refactor of sibling libs, no in-flight branch consolidation. The repo.patch must contain **only** the three named source files plus conventional release artifacts (CHANGELOG entry, version bump, release notes). Anything else = scope creep ‚Üí escalate.\n- Considered & rejected: putting period logic in `shared src/lib/` (premature ‚Äî single consumer, follows the co-located-lib precedent); using a date library (repo has none for this; native `Date` arithmetic is sufficient and dependency-free).\n\n---\n\n## Task breakdown ‚Äî 1 task, 3 story points (delegated to Dev Clone)\n\n### TASK-1 (3 pts) ‚Äî Implement `getFiscalPeriod` + tests + barrel export\n\n**Files to CREATE/MODIFY (exact paths):**\n1. CREATE `src/features/ledger/lib/period.ts`\n2. CREATE `src/features/ledger/lib/period.test.ts`\n3. MODIFY `src/features/ledger/index.ts` ‚Äî add barrel export\n\n**(a) `period.ts` ‚Äî contract:**\n```ts\nexport interface FiscalPeriod {\n  year: number;        // fiscal-year label = calendar year in which the fiscal year STARTS\n  quarter: 1 | 2 | 3 | 4;\n  month: number;       // FISCAL month number 1-12 (1 = first month of the fiscal year)\n  periodStart: Date;   // 1st day of the calendar month containing `date`, local 00:00:00.000\n  periodEnd: Date;     // last day of that calendar month, local 23:59:59.999\n}\nexport function getFiscalPeriod(date: Date, fiscalYearStartMonth?: number): FiscalPeriod;\n```\n- `fiscalYearStartMonth` defaults to `1` (calendar year). The 'period' unit = the **calendar month** containing the date (ERP/bookkeeping convention: a fiscal period is an accounting month).\n- Derivation (use **local** accessors `getFullYear`/`getMonth`/`getDate`; `getMonth` is 0-based, so calMonth = `date.getMonth()+1`):\n  - `fiscalMonth = ((calMonth - fiscalYearStartMonth + 12) % 12) + 1`\n  - `quarter = Math.floor((fiscalMonth - 1) / 3) + 1`\n  - `year = calMonth >= fiscalYearStartMonth ? calYear : calYear - 1`\n  - `periodStart = new Date(calYear, calMonth-1, 1, 0,0,0,0)`\n  - `periodEnd = new Date(calYear, calMonth, 0, 23,59,59,999)` (day 0 of next month = last day of this month; leap Feb‚Üí29 falls out naturally)\n- **Fail loud with `RangeError`** (match sibling-lib convention):\n  - reject when `!(date instanceof Date) || !Number.isFinite(date.getTime())`\n  - reject when `fiscalYearStartMonth` is supplied and not an integer in `1..12` (so `0` and `13` throw)\n- Module must be pure / side-effect-free. Add a short header comment in the style of `round.ts`, and pin the local-time + period-unit conventions in that comment.\n\n**Worked examples (must hold):**\n- `getFiscalPeriod(new Date(2026,0,15))` ‚Üí year 2026, quarter 1, month 1\n- `getFiscalPeriod(new Date(2026,6,1), 7)` ‚Üí year 2026, quarter 1, month 1\n- `getFiscalPeriod(new Date(2026,2,15), 7)` ‚Üí year 2025, quarter 3, month 9\n- `getFiscalPeriod(new Date(2026,11,31))` ‚Üí year 2026, quarter 4, month 12\n\n**(b) `period.test.ts` ‚Äî required cases** (mirror `round.test.ts`: `import assert from \"node:assert/strict\"; import { test } from \"node:test\";`; construct dates with the **numeric** `new Date(y, mIndex, d)` constructor to stay TZ-deterministic ‚Äî never `new Date('2026-01-15')`):\n1. Jan 15, calendar year ‚Üí quarter 1, month 1\n2. Jul 1 with `fiscalYearStartMonth=7` ‚Üí fiscal month 1, quarter 1, year 2026\n3. Dec 31, calendar year ‚Üí quarter 4, month 12\n4. Leap-year Feb 29 (`new Date(2024,1,29)`) ‚Üí `periodEnd` is Feb 29 23:59:59.999 (not Feb 28); no throw\n5. Period boundaries: last day of one period vs first day of next (e.g. assert `periodEnd` of Mar = Mar 31 and `periodStart` of Apr = Apr 1; non-overlapping/contiguous)\n6. Invalid `fiscalYearStartMonth=0` throws `RangeError`; `=13` throws `RangeError`\n7. Non-finite date (`new Date(NaN)`) throws `RangeError`\n\n**(c) `index.ts`** ‚Äî add, alongside the other `./lib/*` re-exports:\n```ts\nexport { type FiscalPeriod, getFiscalPeriod } from \"./lib/period\";\n```\n\n**Validation commands (all must pass):**\n- `npm run typecheck`\n- `npx tsx --test ./src/features/ledger/lib/period.test.ts` (then full `npm test`)\n- `npm run lint`\n\n**DO NOT TOUCH (scope boundary):** any file outside the three listed above. No changes to `round.ts`/`arithmetic.ts`/`format.ts`/`amount.ts`/`trial-balance.ts`/`ingest.ts`, no component/dashboard edits, no money-format consolidation, no dependency additions, no sibling refactors.\n\n**Summary:** ADR 0006 ‚Äî standalone fiscal-period date utility. 1 task, 3 points. Handed off to Dev Clone via `architecture.analysis.completed`.", "content_type": "success", "priority": "normal"}}

