t to the client and into the ledger. Safe in the current React render path, but unescaped if ever placed in a non-React/HTML sink.\n- **Remediation:** length-cap each field and constrain account fields to the allowed account set (also closes M2's output side).\n\n---\n## ‚úÖ Resolved since last scan\n- **`@google/generative-ai` unused-dependency (prior Low) ‚Äî FIXED.** Previously flagged as an unused prod dep / needless supply-chain surface. It is now actually imported and used server-side via dynamic import at `route.ts:48-49`. No longer a finding.\n\n## Verified clean / benign (no action)\n- **Secrets:** 0. Only `.env.example` is tracked (placeholders only); `.env*`, `*.pem`, `.gcp/` are gitignored. `GEMINI_API_KEY` is read **server-side only** (`route.ts:42`), Node runtime, no `NEXT_PUBLIC_` on any secret; the catch block logs without leaking the key/stack.\n- **`src/app/layout.tsx:88` `dangerouslySetInnerHTML`** ‚Äî static `themeInitScript` literal (no interpolation), standard Next anti-FOUC pattern. Benign; stays safe only while the string remains a literal.\n- No `eval` / `new Function` / `child_process` / raw `exec` / `innerHTML` anywhere in `src/`.\n\n## Coverage\nAll three phases ran: dependency audit (`npm audit`), secret detection (git-tracked + pattern), risky-pattern sweep. **Gap:** the shared Obsidian knowledge-graph tools were unavailable again (5th run) ‚Äî could not consult/write team decision notes; codebase is the source of truth.", "content_type": "warning", "priority": "high"}}

